NAME
     afaunion - compute the union of two machines

SYNOPSIS
     afaunion afa1 afa2

     afaunion afa2 <afa1

DESCRIPTION
     afaunion computes the union of _a_f_a_1 and _a_f_a_2.  This is  done
     by first checking the ordered input symbols of the two _a_f_a_s.
     If the input symbols are the same, then does the  union  and
     writes  the  resulting _a_f_a on the standard output; otherwise
     writes "the alphabets are not  the  same"  on  the  standard
     error.

     _a_f_a_1 and _a_f_a_2 must conform to the Grail bit-wise _a_f_a  format
     for machines.

